    <item>
        <title>Sensible Defaults</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;If you&amp;#8217;re using &lt;a href="http://www.capify.org/"&gt;Capistrano&lt;/a&gt; for your deployments and don&amp;#8217;t want to accidentally have master (as opposed to your well-tested branch) deployed to production, it&amp;#8217;s probably a good idea to write your deployment task so that it&amp;#8217;s impossible to deploy anything that&amp;#8217;s not a branch to your production environment. Ahem.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/sneer/blog/~4/394183832" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description>
        <link>http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/sneer/blog/~3/394183832/</link>
